1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:00,962
TL;DR.

2
00:00:00,962 --> 00:00:03,087
This week in 30 seconds:.

3
00:00:03,087 --> 00:00:15,787
Claude Mythos: Anthropic's secret frontier model found 271 Firefox zero-days – and will therefore not be released; only 6 tech giants receive exclusive access for pre-patch purposes.

4
00:00:15,787 --> 00:00:29,650
Compute War: Google secures Anthropic with a $40B deal at a $350B valuation – combined with Amazon's $25B, Anthropic now has access to 10 gigawatts of compute.

5
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:41,137
Sovereign AI: Cohere acquires Aleph Alpha for $20B, financed by Lidl parent Schwarz Group – Europe's most concrete alternative to US AI hyperscalers yet.

6
00:00:41,137 --> 00:00:53,525
DeepSeek: V4-Pro with 1.6 trillion parameters on Huawei chips launches as the world's largest open-weight model – at $0.14/million tokens for V4-Flash.

7
00:00:53,525 --> 00:00:54,775
Story of the Week.

8
00:00:54,775 --> 00:00:58,237
The World's Most Dangerous Model – That You'll Never Use.

9
00:00:58,237 --> 00:01:02,575
271 zero-day vulnerabilities in Firefox alone .

10
00:01:02,575 --> 00:01:18,850
Anthropic's new frontier model "Claude Mythos" is so capable at finding and exploiting security vulnerabilities that its creator isn't even planning a public release – and has instead built an exclusive patching program for six of the world's most powerful tech companies.

11
00:01:18,850 --> 00:01:31,762
Foreign Policy reported exclusively on April 20 about "Project Glasswing": Amazon, Apple, Google, JPMorganChase, Microsoft, and Nvidia receive privileged access to Mythos .

12
00:01:31,762 --> 00:01:39,675
The purpose is defensive – the companies are meant to patch their own systems before a malicious actor could use the same model to attack them.

13
00:01:39,675 --> 00:01:51,100
Mozilla CTO Eric Rescorla publicly confirmed that Mythos identified 271 vulnerabilities in Firefox alone – a browser used by more than two billion people daily.

14
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:58,700
Anthropic describes Mythos as "the most powerful model to date" with cybersecurity as its primary application.

15
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:10,475
The model can autonomously plan and execute multi-stage cyberattacks – a capability level that apparently crosses even Anthropic's threshold between "safe release" and "not justifiable."

16
00:02:10,475 --> 00:02:13,112
No public API access is planned.

17
00:02:13,112 --> 00:02:15,237
"The most powerful model to date."

18
00:02:15,237 --> 00:02:17,887
— Anthropic, quoted via Foreign Policy

19
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:23,275
Why this matters: For security teams, this marks the transition into a new era.

20
00:02:23,275 --> 00:02:36,100
If an AI model can find 271 Firefox bugs in a short time, attackers with similar or stolen systems can do the same – classic patch cycles that take weeks to months are no longer sufficient.

21
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:44,100
"Project Glasswing" is effectively a private early-warning system for six select partners, while the rest of the industry waits.

22
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:56,612
Critical voices: It remains unclear by what criteria the six partners were selected – and why operators of critical infrastructure (utilities, hospitals, government agencies) receive no access.

23
00:02:56,612 --> 00:02:59,187
Who decides whose systems get patched first?

24
00:02:59,187 --> 00:03:10,575
Bottom line: The world's most powerful offensive AI model is currently securing the systems of a handpicked tech elite – everyone else has to hope that nobody else replicates it first.

25
00:03:10,575 --> 00:03:11,912
More Top Stories.

26
00:03:11,912 --> 00:03:17,512
Google Doubles Down: $40 Billion for Anthropic – and 5 Gigawatts of Compute.

27
00:03:17,512 --> 00:03:25,887
The largest single investment in AI history is official: Alphabet is committing up to $40B to Anthropic .

28
00:03:25,887 --> 00:03:34,537
$10B flows immediately at a $350B valuation, with another $30B tied to performance targets.

29
00:03:34,537 --> 00:03:41,462
Additionally, Google Cloud is providing 5 gigawatts of TPU-based compute capacity over five years .

30
00:03:41,462 --> 00:03:55,200
Combined with Amazon's existing $25B deal and its own 5 GW compute package, Anthropic now has access to up to 10 gigawatts of compute  – a reserve that would make even hyperscalers envious.

31
00:03:55,200 --> 00:04:04,837
Anthropic's annual revenue surpassed the $30B mark in April 2026, making the valuation appear less absurd despite its size.

32
00:04:04,837 --> 00:04:15,312
For enterprise customers and developers, this means stability: Anthropic can keep pace in the infrastructure arms race against OpenAI, Google DeepMind, and Meta.

33
00:04:15,312 --> 00:04:23,837
The flip side: with Google and Amazon as primary financiers, Anthropic's "independence" is increasingly a matter of definition.

34
00:04:23,837 --> 00:04:29,487
Cohere + Aleph Alpha: Europe's Only $20 Billion AI Alliance.

35
00:04:30,412 --> 00:04:45,487
The first transatlantic sovereign AI champion is taking shape: Canadian AI company Cohere is acquiring German startup Aleph Alpha, financed through a €500M investment from Schwarz Group (owner of Lidl and Kaufland) .

36
00:04:45,487 --> 00:04:52,575
The combined valuation stands at around $20B, compared to $6.8B for Cohere alone.

37
00:04:52,575 --> 00:05:00,962
Aleph Alpha's 250 employees bring specialized expertise in small language models, European languages, and tokenizers .

38
00:05:00,962 --> 00:05:07,575
"Their focus on small language models, European languages and tokenizers is a really complementary one."

39
00:05:07,575 --> 00:05:09,987
— Aidan Gomez, CEO Cohere

40
00:05:09,987 --> 00:05:25,050
The strategic goal: a sovereign alternative for governments and regulated industries (defense, energy, finance, healthcare, public sector) that distrust US hyperscalers – backed by both the Canadian and German governments .

41
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:33,112
Aleph Alpha's existing customer relationships in Europe – from federal agencies to DAX corporations – are the real asset here.

42
00:05:33,112 --> 00:05:40,737
For European companies and government bodies, this is the most concrete sovereign AI option that has ever existed at this level.

43
00:05:40,737 --> 00:05:54,050
A $20B valuation is still far from Anthropic's $350B – but sovereign AI doesn't compete primarily on capability, but on trust, data privacy, and regulatory compliance.

44
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:59,137
On that terrain, the Cohere–Aleph Alpha combination has genuine strengths.

45
00:05:59,137 --> 00:06:05,562
DeepSeek V4: 1.6 Trillion Parameters on Huawei Chips – at Fraction-of-Cost Pricing.

46
00:06:05,562 --> 00:06:20,450
DeepSeek has released V4-Flash and V4-Pro as a preview, both as Mixture-of-Experts architectures with a 1-million-token context window – developed entirely on Huawei hardware, without Nvidia GPUs .

47
00:06:20,450 --> 00:06:34,812
V4-Pro brings 1.6 trillion total parameters (49B active), making it the world's largest available open-weight model – more than twice the size of V3.2 with 671B parameters .

48
00:06:34,812 --> 00:06:41,012
"Closed the gap with current leading models, both open and closed, on reasoning benchmarks."

49
00:06:41,012 --> 00:06:41,975
— DeepSeek

50
00:06:41,975 --> 00:06:50,800
The price: $0.14 per million input tokens for V4-Flash  – V4-Pro pricing will follow with the full release.

51
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:58,562
The knowledge cutoff is still roughly 3–6 months behind absolute frontier models – but the benchmark catch-up curve is steep.

52
00:06:58,562 --> 00:07:06,487
For teams looking to minimize costs without sacrificing strong reasoning capabilities, DeepSeek V4 is a serious contender.

53
00:07:06,487 --> 00:07:15,037
Politically, the question remains open whether Western companies will be permitted or willing to use Chinese open-weight models for sensitive workloads.

54
00:07:15,037 --> 00:07:15,987
Quick Hits.

55
00:07:15,987 --> 00:07:17,062
Briefly noted:.

56
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:34,862
GPT-5.5: OpenAI unifies Codex and the main model – 82.7% on Terminal-Bench 2.0, immediately available for all paid tiers (Plus, Pro, Business, Enterprise) in ChatGPT and the Codex API .

57
00:07:34,862 --> 00:07:56,275
Agent Economy: Anthropic employees sent AI agents as buyers and sellers into a real test marketplace – 186 completed deals, over $4,000 in total revenue; stronger models achieved objectively better outcomes for their "owners," defining "Agent Quality Gaps" as a new risk for users of weaker agents .

58
00:07:56,275 --> 00:08:17,700
ChatGPT Images 2.0: OpenAI launches gpt-image-2 with up to 4K resolution, ~99% text accuracy, and support for Japanese, Korean, Hindi, and Bengali – DALL-E 2 and DALL-E 3 will be shut down on May 12, 2026; developers must migrate .

59
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:18,825
Tool of the Week.

60
00:08:18,825 --> 00:08:23,875
ComfyUI  – Node-based AI media workstation for creators who want control

61
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:33,212
ComfyUI has raised $30M in Series B funding at a $500M valuation – with Craft Ventures as lead investor .

62
00:08:33,212 --> 00:08:49,762
With over 4 million users, the node-based workflow interface for AI-generated images, videos, and audio has established itself as the de facto standard for creators who want to extract more than 60–80% target quality from prompt-based tools .

63
00:08:49,762 --> 00:08:56,787
"In the world where AI slop is going to be everywhere, the Comfy version of human-in-the-loop approach is going to win out."

64
00:08:56,787 --> 00:08:59,250
— Yoland Yan, CEO ComfyUI

65
00:09:00,175 --> 00:09:11,237
Particularly useful for VFX artists, animators, advertising professionals, and industrial designers who need repeatable, controlled workflows rather than random prompt results.

66
00:09:11,237 --> 00:09:18,075
"ComfyUI artist/engineer" is developing into an independent job title according to the CEO .

67
00:09:18,075 --> 00:09:25,100
Open source, locally runnable, with a massive community plugin library for virtually every media use case.

68
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,250
Fail of the Week.

69
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:29,812
"We silently test-raise your prices – then walk it back"

70
00:09:29,812 --> 00:09:39,525
Anthropic restricted Claude Code without announcement to $100+/month Max plans – instead of the previous $20/month (Pro) .

71
00:09:39,525 --> 00:09:45,925
Only the pricing page was updated; support documentation and community channels remained untouched.

72
00:09:45,925 --> 00:09:59,850
The result: confusion, public backlash on X and Hacker News, and Simon Willison – one of the most influential AI bloggers and educators – publicly signaled a switch to OpenAI Codex for his teaching materials .

73
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:02,537
Within hours, Anthropic walked it back.

74
00:10:02,537 --> 00:10:06,012
Head of Growth Amol Avasare explained after the fact:.

75
00:10:06,012 --> 00:10:10,900
"For clarity, we're running a small test on ~2% of new prosumer signups.

76
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:14,450
Existing Pro and Max subscribers aren't affected."

77
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:26,400
OpenAI seized the moment for its own positioning: Thibault Sottiaux publicly posted that Codex would remain available on the Free and Plus tier ($20) (via simonwillison.net ).

78
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:32,175
That's also marketing – but in this case, targeted precisely at a community that was just frustrated.

79
00:10:32,175 --> 00:10:44,650
Root cause: An A/B pricing test was rolled out without any communication – in a developer community that depends on predictability and trust, since entire workflows are built on pricing assumptions.

80
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:48,037
What we learn: If you're testing prices, communicate it.

81
00:10:48,037 --> 00:10:53,975
Developer communities penalize opacity faster and more durably than any other user group.

82
00:10:53,975 --> 00:10:55,112
Number of the Week.

83
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:58,250
271 Zero-Day Vulnerabilities

84
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:09,275
Exactly 271 security vulnerabilities were found by Claude Mythos in Firefox alone – confirmed by Mozilla's CTO following participation in "Project Glasswing" .

85
00:11:09,275 --> 00:11:20,625
The number makes tangible why Anthropic has no plans for a public release: an attacker with access to Mythos would have a ready catalog of exploitable vulnerabilities before patches exist.

86
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:26,437
And that's just Firefox – not Windows, not macOS, not Chrome, not Android.

87
